# Vendored runtime deps for the publish tool — committed on purpose.
# The plugin cache is a git copy of this repo, and a site's `file:` pin symlinks the tool
# out of that cache, so Node resolves the tool's require()s from the cache location. The
# deps must travel with it or builds fail with "Cannot find module". This negation is LAST
# so it overrides the earlier node_modules/, dist/, and bin/ rules for this one subtree.
# See tools/publish/README.md ("Vendored dependencies").
!tools/publish/node_modules/
!tools/publish/node_modules/**
# ...but never the npm-generated cruft: .bin holds machine-local (absolute-target)
# symlinks that would ship as dangling links, and .package-lock.json is regenerable.
tools/publish/node_modules/.bin/
tools/publish/node_modules/.package-lock.json
tools/publish/node_modules/**/.package-lock.json
